President Donald Trump joined Fox & Friends via phone to discuss various topics including Hurricane Michael, healthcare, the economy, and progress with North Korea. He emphasized the commitment to accelerating the recovery efforts for areas affected by the hurricane. Trump also highlighted the economic success under his administration, citing low unemployment rates and high median incomes for African Americans. He criticized Bernie Sanders' healthcare plan, arguing that it would bankrupt the United States and result in inferior quality of care. Trump praised Secretary Mike Pompeo for his work on denuclearization with North Korea. He also mentioned the administration's efforts to renegotiate trade deals and criticized Democrats for obstructing the rebuilding of the military and the border wall.